### Bug P2: Collision tile coordinate math is wrong for negative positions
Status: Fixed locally on branch `codex` (pending commit hash).
Impact: collision now uses floor-based world-to-tile conversion, so negative positions map to correct tile indices.
Recommendation: keep floor conversion centralized in one helper to avoid future regressions.
Priority: Resolved

### Bug P3: Tilemap indexing assumes rectangular rows but debug/collision index math does not enforce it
Status: Fixed locally on branch `codex` (pending commit hash).
Impact: collision/debug systems now validate rectangular tilemap rows and use canonical column-count index math for blocked-tile lookups.
Recommendation: additionally validate and reject ragged rows in `TilemapLoader` as defense-in-depth.
Priority: Resolved

### Bug P4: InputManager API contract comments contradict runtime usage
Evidence: `InputManager` header says `BeginFrame()` must run before `SDL_PollEvent` (`src/core/InputManager.h:9-16`), but `Game::Run()` currently calls `PumpEvents()` first, then `BeginFrame()` (`src/core/Game.cpp:52-54`).
Risk: future maintenance regression where someone "fixes" call order to match the comment and reintroduces one-frame-late input.
Recommendation: update comments to match the correct current ordering (events pumped first, snapshot second).
Priority: Medium
